http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Vijayawada/Andhra-Bank-to-invest-Rs.-5000-crore-in-AP/article13995482.ece

The Andhra Bank (AB) has signed a Memorandum of Understanding (MoU) with the State government to invest Rs. 5,000 crore in the State.The MoU was signed at the ongoing Confederation of Indian Industry (CII) Partnership Summit in Visakhatpatnam. Andhra Bank Managing Director and CEO Suresh N Patel said the bank had expressed its interest to invest Rs. 5,000 crore in next three years.Industrial growthThe investments would be for industrial development across the State, including Capital region.The MoU was aimed at developing industry in the State, he said.A lot of activity was taking place in Andhra Pradesh.There is a tremendous potential in housing sector and industry in the State, he said.